<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Lucas Critique suggests that economic policy evaluations should:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Focus only on historical relationships</option>
            <option letter="b">Consider how expectations change behavior</option>
            <option letter="c">Ignore international factors</option>
            <option letter="d">Rely solely on monetary aggregates</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Lucas Critique argues that policy evaluations must account for how people's expectations and behavior change in response to policy changes, rather than relying solely on historical relationships.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>The sterilization of foreign exchange interventions involves:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Allowing the money supply to change</option>
            <option letter="b">Offsetting changes in the money supply</option>
            <option letter="c">Fixing exchange rates</option>
            <option letter="d">Eliminating capital controls</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Sterilization occurs when central banks offset the effects of foreign exchange interventions on the domestic money supply through offsetting open market operations.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>According to the monetary approach to exchange rates, a higher interest rate will:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Always cause the currency to appreciate</option>
            <option letter="b">Always cause the currency to depreciate</option>
            <option letter="c">Cause appreciation only if due to monetary contraction</option>
            <option letter="d">Have no effect on exchange rates</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The monetary approach suggests that higher interest rates cause currency appreciation only if they result from monetary contraction rather than higher expected inflation.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>The Tobin tax was proposed to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Reduce income inequality</option>
            <option letter="b">Decrease currency speculation</option>
            <option letter="c">Increase government revenue</option>
            <option letter="d">Promote international trade</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Tobin tax was proposed as a small tax on foreign exchange transactions to reduce short-term currency speculation and market volatility.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
